Uses of Interface
com.cyc.kb.KBTerm

  • Packages that use KBTerm 
    Package Description
    com.cyc.kb
    Provides basic interfaces for manipulating CycL-based java objects, both for the purpose of making assertions and for retrieving terms and values via simple queries.
    com.cyc.kb.client
    The implementation of various interfaces specified in com.cyc.kb, refer to that package for a more detailed discussion of using the API.

    • Uses of KBTerm in com.cyc.kb

      Subinterfaces of KBTerm in com.cyc.kb 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  BinaryPredicate
      The interface for KBPredicates that take exactly two arguments.
      interface  Context
      The interface for KBIndividuals that correspond to CycL microtheories.
      interface  FirstOrderCollection
      The interface for KBCollections whose members are all KBIndividuals.
      interface  KBCollection
      The top-level interface corresponding to Cyc #$Collection.
      interface  KBFunction
      The interface for Cyc functions.
      interface  KBIndividual
      The top-level interface for Cyc #$Individuals.
      interface  KBPredicate
      The interface for Cyc predicates.
      interface  LogicalConnective
      The interface for logical connectives of the CycL language, such as #$and and #$or.
      interface  Quantifier
      The interface for Cyc quantifiers, such as #$thereExists.
      interface  Relation
      The common interface for KBPredicate and KBFunction.
      interface  ScopingRelation
      The interface for Relations that determine the scope of one or more Variables.
      interface  SecondOrderCollection
      The interface for KBCollections whose instances are FirstOrderCollections.
